text: Maria Lorena González (born February 20, 1977) is an American lawyer and former politician. She was a member of the Seattle City Council from position 9. She was the first Latina elected to the council. She was a candidate for mayor of Seattle in 2021 but lost to Bruce Harrell. ==References== Category:1977 births Category:Living people Category:Politicians from Seattle Category:Democratic Party (United States) politicians
